the airport and fifteen minutes into Kailua Kona town.

host_about:
Our ohana (Hawaiian for home) and the general ambiance of this space is the essence of relaxed and peaceful.   It is easy to enjoy the best of any destination, if you meet nice people, see interesting sights (from temples to museums), or simply enjoy the coast, swimming, sunbathing, walking or snorkeling.

name: Lotus Garden/Lotus Cottage Downtown 3BR
description: Welcome to historic old Hawaii. Charming old refurbished COTTAGE with 3 bedrooms -delightful walled garden compound. This vacation cottage is set in a garden with 3 other cottages. It is set directly behind a renovated 1940s building with street frontage. Early bird discounts and longer stay discounts available.
neighborhood_overview:
Hilo has a 'retro vibe' that is charming to many who come here. Hilo has a more than average number of artists & creatives.There is a fusion of cultures and cuisines which make for some interesting small restaurants around town and there are several places to eat and listen to live music.
Browsers might enjoy the thrift stores or vintage stores. The 'famous' Hilo Farmers Market is one block from this property.

Hilo is a great place for guests to enjoy slowing down & it is a great base for those with a long 'bucket list' of sights on the East side of the island:
lava viewing, stargazing, botanical garden, waterfalls, Waipio valley and more. Hilo is central to all of these sights.
host_about:
Aloha I'm Megan. Meet Jasper also. We've been working to create a colorful atmosphere for visitors that reflects the beauty of the tropics. Both of us enjoy helping guests feel comfortable so that they can relax and enjoy all the magic of this wet and wild side of the island. 

Hilo could become known as 'the town that time forgot' because it has the flavor of an older, slower Hawaii. In that way we are pretty easy going and relaxed ourselves. We have two guest cottages and a romantic 1 bedroom apartment here at The Lotus Garden. This is a property that features two garden courtyards, stone Buddha statues, a fish pond and an abundance of tropical plants and trees. . The Lotus Garden is reminiscent of the former 'sugar cane plantation days' when houses were clustered together so that there was a sense of community in the way people lived. Here Travelers meet other travelers in passing. Another wonderful feature of The Lotus Garden is that we are right in the center of town. Guests enjoy being a block away from the Farmer's Market and within walking distance of our cafes, restaurants, galleries and even Hilo's own Kava Bar. 

Just ask us. .. we know some great little beach parks close by and some special things to do around Hilo..  

... Our latest creed to live by? "Now is a really good time!" And so it is..

name: Winter SALE Enchanting Rainforest Hideaway 2 Acres
description:
Winter Sale! Prices dropped for March. The Enchanting Rainforest Hideaway is a very private, well equipped, custom vacation home which stands alone on 2 private acres surrounded by a lush tropical rainforest which gives you the experience of old Hawaiian style simple elegance.
The cabin is the only dwelling on the property and no one else lives or works on the 2 acres.
host_about: We are a fun loving, adventurous couple,  living in the jungles of east Hawaii.  We have traveled, and travel,  extensively. We love visiting exotic locations and meeting people from all over the world.    Connie is a semi- retired, celebrity wardrobe stylist originally from Hollywood.  Andrew, originally from Australia, is a building contractor and FEO Officer/tanker driver for the Hawaiian Paradise Park Volunteer Fire Department . Connie currently  is a yoga instructor who runs her own studio on a 40 acre permaculture farm in Pahoa and leads yoga retreats on the island of Paros, Greece during the summer. Choosing a simpler life, we moved to Pahoa in 2001 to fulfill our dream of off-grid, sustainable living.   Our home is  up the road from the Rainforest Hideaway on a separate property we developed ourselves with machetes and a lot of sweat.  We hand built our rammed earth home, made from volcanic cinder and inorganic soil from old sugar cane fields,  and grow most of own own food organically.

name: Dragonfly Cabin
description: Private Cabin Sleeps 4  with Ocean and Lava Field Views. Includes Private Bath. These 20’ x 24’ spacious cabins boast a beautiful screened in porch offering spectacular views of the new lava fields with an ocean backdrop. Each 14’ x 14’ bedroom offers a comfortable queen bed, 2 bunk beds, closet, desk and chair.
neighborhood_overview: Our location is pristine. Mango Road is a sacred authentic, well preserved landmark to the ancient Hawaiians and so beautiful.
host_about:
Kirpal Meditation and Ecological Center is a half mile from the ocean on the eastern tip of the Big Island of Hawaii, approximately seven miles from the small village of Pahoa. The 10-acre ocean-view property is blessed with average daytime temperatures of 85° F year-round, and 65° F at night, with cool, fragrant trade winds, surrounding tropical flora, including old growth mangoes, nearby swimming, surfing and snorkeling.

This property was once a papaya farm and is now newly planted with bamboo, papaya, palms, banana and many other fruit trees. The octagonal Balinese meditation pavilion is set among shade-trees with an expansive view of the ocean. The island wildlife is all around us – a variety of birds by day and at night there's the pleasant chirping of Coqui frogs – and there are no snakes. Natural wonders include Volcanoes National Park, for lava and crater viewing, volcanically heated warm ponds and steam vents (as outdoor saunas) and other wonders of the lush tropics.

Kmec opened in the summer of 2008 for pre-arranged seasonal meditation retreats and private meditation-vacations on request. Additionally, we would like to extend our welcome to Big Island travelers offering cozy cottages and open air kitchen and bath. We offer daily free meditation instructions and practices at our beautiful Balinese meditation pavillion. Additionally, we offer Yoga and nature tours upon guest's request (donations accepted).

neighborhood_overview: Our location is pristine. Mango Road is a sacred authentic, well preserved landmark to the ancient Hawaiians and so beautiful.
host_about:
Kirpal Meditation and Ecological Center is a half mile from the ocean on the eastern tip of the Big Island of Hawaii, approximately seven miles from the small village of Pahoa. The 10-acre ocean-view property is blessed with average daytime temperatures of 85° F year-round, and 65° F at night, with cool, fragrant trade winds, surrounding tropical flora, including old growth mangoes, nearby swimming, surfing and snorkeling.

This property was once a papaya farm and is now newly planted with bamboo, papaya, palms, banana and many other fruit trees. The octagonal Balinese meditation pavilion is set among shade-trees with an expansive view of the ocean. The island wildlife is all around us – a variety of birds by day and at night there's the pleasant chirping of Coqui frogs – and there are no snakes. Natural wonders include Volcanoes National Park, for lava and crater viewing, volcanically heated warm ponds and steam vents (as outdoor saunas) and other wonders of the lush tropics.

Kmec opened in the summer of 2008 for pre-arranged seasonal meditation retreats and private meditation-vacations on request. Additionally, we would like to extend our welcome to Big Island travelers offering cozy cottages and open air kitchen and bath. We offer daily free meditation instructions and practices at our beautiful Balinese meditation pavillion. Additionally, we offer Yoga and nature tours upon guest's request (donations accepted).

- Surfing: Ke‘ei and Kahaluu
- Big Island Bees
- Coffee tours

neighborhood_overview:
Waikīkī (/waɪkiːˈkiː/; Hawaiian: [vɐiˈkiːˈkiː] or [wɐiˈkiːˈkiː]) is a beachfront neighborhood of Honolulu, on the south shore of the island of Oʻahu, in Hawaii, United States. Waikiki is best known for Waikīkī Beach, the white sand beach shoreline fronting the neighborhood.

Waikīkī is home to public places including Kapiʻolani Park, Fort de Russy Military Reservation, Kahanamoku Lagoon, Kūhiō Beach Park, and Ala Wai Harbor.

name: Taxes Included in Nightly Rate - Prime Location
description: Our ideal location will provide you with a great way to get the most out of your Maui vacation. We have endeavored to make our condo well equipped for your comfort. A renown beach is just across the street and dining options are equally close.
host_about:
My wife and I are early retirees who have been enjoying the beauty of Hawaii for 20 years.  After having visited all of the major Hawaiian Islands, we realized that there is no other place that offers what Maui offers.  Living on the East Coast, it is a long flight, but it is well worth the time to reach paradise.

In our Maui travels, we explored  north, east, south and west and stayed in each of these locations.  There was no question that Kihei offered us the best weather, variety of beaches, and access to great restaurants, shopping and golf.  We limited our search for a condo to the KAM I, II and III area and were fortunate enough to find our ideal location.

We are an active couple.  The South Kihei location affords us the ability to explore a wide variety of beaches each with their own personality.  Our daily walks originate from our condo, and our more aggressive hiking locations are equally convenient.  When we want to explore beyond the Kihei/Wailea/Makena area, other areas of Maui are very accessible.

name: Ocean Front Luxury Condo - Swim with the turtles
description:
Our condo is outside the Lahaina fire zone. The pictures represent how it looks now

Ocean front ground floor condo at Kuleana - a small gated resort stretching over 5 acres of ocean front tropical garden. The resort features two private beaches (seasonal) located in the middle of a Green Sea Turtle Marine Sanctuary. Observe turtles feeding off the underwater rocks as well as the occasional visit of turtles resting on shore.

All taxes and resort fees are included in the nightly rate.
neighborhood_overview:
Kuleana is a small and private gated resort with access to our own private beach (seasonal) and snorkel cove where turtles come in to feed. Unlike many other places we have a very nice garden that is very well maintained.
The surrounding neighborhood include farmers market every Mon, Wed and Friday - only 15 min walk. Across from the farmers market is a public beach park with a playground and low water for young children.
From Honoapiilani Park you can walk on a beach path all the way to Hanakao'o Beach Park. Access to Honoapiilani Park is across the street from Time market.
10 min driving from Lahaina an old and charming whaling city.
5 min north is the Napili beach and a bit further north is Honolua Bay a marine sanctuary perfect for snorkeling.
host_about:
We bought our condo on Maui in 2008. It is our second home and not an investment rental. This means all furniture, kitchen, appliances etc are based on our living preferences.
What makes Kuleana special is the grounds - we have a real garden with plenty of flowers and birds, we have our own beaches, large pool and BBQ at the tip of the water.
To us this place is our ultimate relaxation and the place we turn to when we need a "breather".

host_about:
I studied Neuroscience and Psychology at UC Berkeley and went on to found Merlock L.L.C

I've traveled extensively to England, Germany, France, Italy, India, Thailand, South Africa, Australia, New Zealand, Vietnam, Cambodia, Mexico, Hawaii, Ukraine, and Israel.

Merlock L.L.C. is a web hosting and I.T. consulting business that builds customized software for businesses to enhance productivity. We are also innovators of green energy equipment such as devices that recycle used cooking oil into cost effective vehicle fuel.

My dream is to use the profits of our labor to start a non-profit company that will help disadvantaged people around the world, afford medical care. Specifically a program that will send doctors from the US to the third world, to train mid-level healthcare workers to effectively treat the sick. I believe that everyone should have equal access to healthcare, regardless of socioeconomic status. 

While in college I owned a company that produced raves and concerts near San Francisco. While I don't produce raves anymore, I still run f8gear.com on the side, which sells music. 

I joke around a lot and act like a kid when I'm around cute little pets. I love plants and growing plants. If I get an avocado (yum!) I plant the seed. 

One indicator of successful people is their ability to choose a greater reward that takes longer to achieve, versus an inferior reward that takes less time. I typically wait the longer period for the greater reward. 

Favorite Quotes: 
"Be ashamed to die until you have won some victory for humanity."
Horace Mann, address at Antioch College, 1859
US educator (1796 - 1859)

"The Era of Procrastination, of Half-Measures, of Soothing and Baffling Expedients, of Delays, is coming to its Close. In its Place We are Entering a Period of Consequences."-Sir Winston Churchill, November 12, 1936

host_about: I am originally from San Diego and moved to NYC 18 years ago and as much as I love NYC I need a getaway and Maui for me is pure paradise. I rented at the Palms several times and fell in love with the property but was never that happy with the units I rented I think because I usually got carpeted units which I dislike and the entertainment features were old fashioned and I love to spend my evenings at home cooking and enjoying good movie. I am a Hairstylist and photographer in NYC and have a love for the right lighting so you allways look your best. Peter Lik is a photgrapher that has inspired me to capture beautiful landscapes and I print the on fujiflexchrome crystal archive paper which is light sensitive which is why I have everyting on dimmers. I also want to say that living in NYC I am exposed to the latest trends and styles. I love hotels like the W because they have a modern but simple way of making life feel new and refreshing and the old hawaiian style with wicker, floral prints and old hawaiian art is just so last decade I needed to go contemporary. With 2 nonstop flights to Honolulu from NYC I can ony hope that my style will enspire you to stay with me.

Beaches in Paia

name: Volcano Artist Cottage
description: Our romantic Volcano Artist Cottage is located adjacent to Hawaii Volcanoes National Park on a 3-acre historic garden estate.  Our intimate cottage has a queen sized bed, a   kitchenette, stocked with breakfast fixings.  Receive 10% off all purchases at award-winning Café Ono and our fine  art gallery.   We offer free Wifi, cable TV,  and library for our cottage guests.
neighborhood_overview:
Volcano Village has been hailed as a model "gateway town" to a major national park. Instead of strip malls, fast food restaurants and hotel chains, visitors approaching Hawaii Volcanoes National Park see...trees. Most houses, and even businesses, are tucked back in the cool high-altitude tropical rainforest. They're surrounded by native ohia trees, luxurious giant tree ferns, and native birds found nowhere else on earth. It's place where you can have all the privacy you want. At night, guests at the Artist's Cottage share the grounds only with Nobel the rescued rabbit—but are still only a short walk from the village center. It’s the sort of place where people not only feel safe to go for a walk at night but will give a friendly wave to strangers.


Such a place draws a unique breed of resident. Geologists, artists, nature lovers from all over the world, as ethnically diverse as they are tolerant and creative, call Volcano "home." It's a great place to have fascinating
host_about:
A Native New Yorker, who came to Hawaii on vacation over 40 years ago and never left!  Ira is the Director/Founded of Volcano Garden Arts, created on a historic 1908 Garden Estate. Today, it boasts a beautiful Native Hawaiian Garden, Art Gallery and Award winning Café Ono, which has a gourmet vegetarian menu. As a full-time Artist, Ira’s work is collected throughout the US, Europe and Japan. The Art gallery features Ira’s works as well as works from over 100 local artists. 
Ira enjoys hosting visitors from across the globe, sharing his beautiful gardens and art work. He is a gracious and open host and enjoys sharing stories.

I owned the Blue Ginger Gallery in Kainaliu, Hawaii for 37 years, showcasing over 70 local artists/crafts persons work and my own hand painted silks!
I love the ocean, snorkeling, paddle board, bike riding, kayaking and wind surfing! I have skied Mauna Kea on several occasions then body surf at Hapuna Beach.

This 1,000 sq. ft. cottage is a beautifully appointed, custom-built retreat offering ocean views and a private outdoor spa. With tropical hardwoods throughout, it comfortably sleeps 4, with a queen bed in the bedroom and loft.

The spacious great room features a cathedral ceiling, a well-equipped kitchen, dining area, and living room for your enjoyment. The large bathroom boasts granite floors and counters, a shower, tub, and a washer/dryer.
neighborhood_overview: We are in the country...very rural, peaceful and quiet with the historic village of Hawi within walking distance. This quaint and lively village has many excellent restaurants, art galleries, local shops, a popular coffee shop and live music for your enjoyment. Ocean swimming is just 10 minutes away and world class beaches, resorts, and golf just 30 minutes away. Nearby there are numerous hikes to waterfalls, sea cliffs and rain forests.

neighborhood_overview:
With countless captivating beaches, near-perfect weather year-round, and panoramic views everywhere you look, it’s hard to argue that Hawaii is anything other than a tropical island oasis! The Hawaiian Islands are incredibly unique, unlike anywhere else in the world. That is clearly evident in everything from our breathtaking scenery to our all-encompassing Aloha spirit!

Maui has been voted the "Best Island in the World" for over 23 years. With daytime temperatures ranging from roughly 85 degrees F during the winter, it's easy to see why Maui is such a popular destination choice and the #1 island in the world.

Here’s why I think the South side of the island (where Kihei is located) is the best place to stay. South Maui really has it all! ;)

The sunny South shores of Kihei offer 6 miles of popular, sun kissed beaches with warm, balmy days and cool, tropical nights.

Typically, humidity levels in Kihei are VERY LOW and the annual rainfall
host_about:
Aloha from Maui!

Congratulations on your decision to book a vacation in sunny Maui, Hawaii; the #1 island in the world for over 25 years.  :)

I would be honored to help you choose accommodations in Maui that fit your needs, desires, and budget. 

As a full-time resident on Maui for over 15 years, I am very familiar with all that this wonderful Island has to offer.  I absolutely love my job as both an owner and property manager of vacation rentals on Maui.  The fact that I get to help others plan their Hawaiian vacation and/or relocation to the magical island of Maui is literally the icing on top of the cupcake!

If you are wanting to purchase property on Maui, I am a licensed realtor in the State of Hawai'i, own a property management company in Maui, and am also a certified Home Staging Expert.  I would love to speak with you and answer any questions you might have about vacation rentals on Maui.

In addition to managing lots of amazing properties directly across the street from the awesome, sun kissed beaches of south Maui, I am also the proud owner of my own vacation rentals.   The condos I own are called Tracy’s Tropical Treasures.  They are listed on Airbnb as Tracy's Tropical Treasure #1 (Ocean View), Tracy's Tropical Treasure #2 (Corner Penthouse), Tracy's Tropical Treasure #3 (Ocean View), and my newest addition, Paradise Awaits You! Tracy's Tropical Treasure #4 (Ocean View, Central A.C., and double pane windows, so no road noise inside the condo).  *Tracy’s Tropical Treasure #3 and Paradise Awaits You! Tracy's Tropical Treasure #4 both house up to 4 guests.  :)

Tracy’s Tropical Treasures were Named the #1 Vacation Rentals in all of Maui in 2016.

In November, 2019, I was RANKED #1 again.  ;)

In July of 2022, I was ranked #1 in Kihei for the fourth time.

I have worked very hard for these achievements and on every single occasion, it was one of the best days of my life when I received confirmation that I had won the award.  

I look forward to speaking with you, helping you with your Maui vacation/relocation, and sharing my ALOHA spirit.  I have been in the hospitality industry for over 25 years, and it's really how I choose to live my life.  Pampering guests is my #1 priority!  

* With well over 1000 bookings on the 4 rentals I personally own, I am extremely proud and take great pride in the fact that I have so many wonderful reviews.  Please feel free to check out all the reviews on Airbnb for the proof.   Customer Service is very important to me!

I am also very proud that I have been with Airbnb since 2009 and have also been a "SUPERHOST” since the program was created.  In July of 2022, I earned Superhost status for the 33rd consecutive time.  

Airbnb is, without a doubt, the BEST vacation rental platform of all!  

When Airbnb was first created, I was one of only eight listings in all of Maui.  My claim to fame is that Brian Chesky, himself, actually called me.  Brian is one of the three Airbnb founders.  Back then, I had also listed my car on Airbnb, and Brian said I was the first person to ever list a car on his platform.  He thought it was interesting, and we had a very nice telephone conversation.

By the end of 2020, Maui had over 18,000 vacation rental listings.  The Airbnb platform has grown exponentially.  I am truly honored to be a part of it all; both as an owner and as a property manager and will continue to tell everyone how wonderful Airbnb is for hosts and travelers alike.

Everybody, no matter where they are, can live ALOHA.  Maui is a great way to unlock the positive spirit within all of us.....

Make it a great day!
Tracy O'Reilly R(S)
~ Owner of Tracy’s Tropical Treasures #1 through #4 (these are my personal vacation rentals which were Named the #1 Vacation Rentals in all of Maui for both 2016 and 2019, and then named #1 in Kihei in July of 2022 for the fourth time)
~ Hawai’i Realtor 
(Licensed on all Islands)

name: Wind, Waves and Comfort 25' from the Ocean
description: The condo is appointed like a 5 star hotel without the price tag!  A vacation condo should feel like home (but better :-). I've filled it with things I love: art, a guitar, a jellyfish lamp and more... so hopefully you'll love it too!It's a beautiful space, 25ft from the ocean with a remodeled kitchen, bathroom, A/C and workstation/internet ideal for remote work (and if you don't need to work, it's a lovely desk for writing postcards). It's also a short walk to sandy beaches & restaurants.
neighborhood_overview:
There's a sandy beach a 1/4 miles to the South that's an easy walk. It's a great, safe beach with ok snorkeling. Better snorkeling can be found at Ka'anapali beach (5 min.) or Honolua Bay (15 min). A less crowded beach is about 1 mile away.

Restaurants and limited shopping are within a couple blocks. For more extensive shopping, you'll need to drive 5 min to Ka'anapali/Whaler's Village or drive 10 min to Lahaina.
host_about:
Hi, I'm Jim Tierney. I live most of the year in San Francisco and escape to Maui whenever I get tired of the foggy weather. I run a small software company and have the good fortune of being able to work anywhere there's an internet connection. Luckily that's the case with Maui, so whenever I get an urge for whale watching, diving, or laying in the sun it's no problem coming over. I love diving and the diving in Maui is spectacular, there are some really beautiful spots. I also have a passion for photography, particularly whales and outdoor scenes, so you'll see some of my work on the walls of the unit.

I hope you'll check out my place. I put a lot of work into it making sure it was a livable space for when I'm there. So I think the standards I have for the condo is much higher than most rental units.

I bought this because I'll be there about two months of the year and I wanted something on the ocean. A friend of mine lives in the same building so I was very familiar with the property and all it offered (ok, so mostly it offered the ocean about 20 feet way :-). It's amazing to watch the sun set during the summer, see the whales during the winter, and listen to the waves all year long.

name: The Birdcage, Waikiki Hideaway
description:
This apartment IS NOT effected by the Honolulu law restricting vacation rentals.

The Birdcage is an apartment perfectly located less than 30 steps from the beach and a short walk from the center of Waikiki. This makes a great home base for exploring Honolulu and the rest of Oahu. The Birdcage is a breezy and bright studio giving you clear views of the Koolau Mountains.
neighborhood_overview:
Kapiolani Park is just across the street and offers the Honolulu Zoo, Waikiki Aquarium, the Royal Hawaiian Bandstand, tennis courts, soccer fields, archery ranges, weekend art shows and the city's Sunset on the Beach free concerts and movies - all this in its 500 green acres.

One of the main reasons for coming to Hawaii is of course the sun and sand. Surfing, stand up paddle boardling, outrigger canoeing, swimming and simply lounging on the beach are all just a few steps from the Birdcage.

Hawaii is the crossroads of the Pacific and its culinary offerings reflect that abundantly, so while the Birdcage has a kitchen and microwave, you are a short walk away from countless cafes and restaurants catering to every taste and price range. Similarly, if you can get yourself out of the water and away from the beach there is a lot of shopping to be done in Waikiki, and the many other shopping venues just a short drive away.
host_about: Born and raised in Honolulu, I currently live on the Mainland, but spend a lot of time in Hawaii. name: Kailua-Kona Oceanfront Delight on a Budget!
description: This is a sweet little budget-friendlier oceanfront townhouse in the Keauhou Kona Surf and Racquet Club (KKSRC).  It is NOT fancy but it is very clean, has most of what anyone would need AND the views are spectacular.  It is loved and enjoyed by many different couples and groups of guests each year. :)
host_about: I love to travel!  I've been very blessed to enjoy traveling as a child while my dad was in the military and then as an adult for my job and with my husband.  We began visiting Hawaii in 1999 and our annual visits turned into our first purchase of a vacation home in 2006.  It was on our 4th trip to the Big Island of Hawaii and during our 2nd stay at the Keauhou Kona Surf and Racquet Club that we began looking for our own place.  The diversity of this island paradise and the wonderful snorkeling and the lovely townhouse settings made all the other complexes pale in comparison on our searches - we purchased townhouse #59 and returned for our fifth trip to completely redo the unit (tile to ceiling) in preparation for personal and guest visits.  We still feel the same way about this wonderful place and now own a second, completely oceanfront unit (#196) in this same lovely complex.  And, it's only gotten better.  Our goal in rentals is to offer what we'd want and expect in a unit if we were traveling.  Super clean, well maintained, simple and beautful decor, plenty of space to pack away our suitcases and settle in comfortably, good beds & linens, and complete kitchens for at home meals whenever we like.  Fortunately for us, many of our guests appreciate and expect the same type of accomodation and we have several guests or groups of guests that have become repeat visitors to our lovely place/s.  All have said this is the best place they've found and the first place they check for return visits.  We love and appreciate all of our guests but even more so our repeat or referred guests.  We'd be delighted to welcome you and your friends to a stay in paradise. Our motto in life - pay it forward; be the first to do the right thing; set the right example; good karma will follow you.  Our guests should know that we will do everything to help them enjoy their stay with us.  It's a point of pride for us - no cutting corners, etc...we want and expect that guests continue to say how nice they expected it to be and how much nicer it actually was.  And, if there's ever a problem; resolving it is our top priority.  We don't want our guests to worry or be inconvenieced wherever possible.

name: Sundeck Suite Kohala Country Haven Big Isle aptmt.
description:
Perfect vacation hideaway for 1-6; price for 2.; $25 night extras.Unique "old Hawaiian-style ranchito".Relax with family, friends; big private deck, panoramic views: pastures, gardens,Maui across the sea, spectacular sunsets. Exciting adventures:zipline,snorkle,kayak famous ditch;whales in season;walk country roads; hike,explore wilderness, historic sites. Easy drives awesome array of beaches, rugged coastline, gorgeous Kohala Mountain Road, Resorts.
Our diverse North Kohala,"No ka oe",the best!
If guests need less than two nights,usually at the last moment, they will have to talk with Bobi and there will be an extra charge.
neighborhood_overview: Kohala Country Adventures Guesthouse is 1/4 mile up a country road,near the famous Statue of Kamehameha,the king who united the Hawaiian islands. You'll enjoy the diversity of shops,restaurants, cultural events,scenery from tropical valleys,exotic plants,ancient fishing villages on the rocky desert coast. North Kohala is in a class by itself,"out of the mix",but close enough to enjoy resorts,white sand beaches,and our  local ecotours,fabulous cuisine and unique gifts of gorgeous woodwork,jewelry,clothing,crafts! Our weather is usually excellent about 80degrees almost all year in the daytime;just the right amount of rain  and breezes(usually). We've lived here 40 years and love North Kohala more each day! It's an honor to share our treasures with appreciative guests.
host_about:
For 48 


years I've loved living in awesome North Kohala, fell in love with my special property when I first saw it in 1974, raised 3 children "roughing it" but loving adventures in a rural community, adopted 6 and fostered 7, taught school as a sub, K-12, painted landscapes in oil around the island before the family expanded to 9+ diverse kids, now want to resume my passion for creativity, hosted many musicians and folks interested in sustainable living, healthy choices, loving each other, God and country, and appreciation for our uniquely wonderful treasures here at the end of the rainbow.
I've really enjoyed meeting guests from all over the world and have made some lifetime friendships. Come visit! We hope you'll fall in love with the joys of North Kohala, create wonderful memories with family and friends, (even business partners) and return for many visits!  My daughter reminds me to "always keep smiling"…it's catching!
